WEBVTT

00:00.086 --> 00:01.686
Previously on "Blood & Oil"...

00:01.710 --> 00:02.977
How long have you been screwing my father?

00:03.005 --> 00:05.289
- No, I care about you.
- But you love him.

00:05.797 --> 00:08.117
We're being investigated
by the U.S. government.

00:08.141 --> 00:12.203
They think that we got our hands
on a U.S.G.S. report illegally.

00:12.228 --> 00:13.995
This case you're building
against my father,

00:14.020 --> 00:15.148
it's airtight, right?

00:15.173 --> 00:15.905
Absolutely.

00:16.015 --> 00:16.921
I'm in.

00:16.946 --> 00:19.246
We found a financial backer to stake us.

00:19.271 --> 00:21.971
Annie Briggs. Hap's first wife.

00:21.996 --> 00:23.890
So, you're backing Billy?

00:24.304 --> 00:28.228
Not so much backing Billy,
as I am coming after you.

00:28.263 --> 00:29.562
We leave him here. We walk away.

00:29.598 --> 00:30.630
Oh, God.

00:30.665 --> 00:32.732
They found the man that attacked me.

00:32.767 --> 00:33.900
Did you do something to him?

00:33.935 --> 00:35.668
I had nothing to do with that.

00:35.704 --> 00:37.003
They don't expect Gary to live.

00:37.038 --> 00:38.805
- What?
- Or to ever wake up.

00:38.840 --> 00:39.906
We don't have to worry about it.

00:44.985 --> 00:47.052
Need a little help in here.

00:47.077 --> 00:49.611
I need somebody to hold his
arms. Got to get this tube in.

00:49.636 --> 00:51.036
No, no.

00:51.319 --> 00:52.619
I got to get this tube back in.

00:52.654 --> 00:54.734
Billy!

00:54.759 --> 00:56.526
- He's getting hypoxic.
- Billy!

00:56.699 --> 00:58.599
What did he say?

00:59.828 --> 01:02.328
SVT! I need 6 of adenosine, stat!

01:02.364 --> 01:03.930
6 of adenosine.

01:04.593 --> 01:06.794
Billy LeFever!

01:09.632 --> 01:11.237
Yes, I know.

01:11.273 --> 01:14.007
I said I'd never set foot
back in Rock Springs,

01:14.042 --> 01:17.360
but I think this is really
gonna be a good time.

01:18.476 --> 01:20.179
You know what? I got to call you back.

01:22.257 --> 01:23.950
Turn the car around, now.

01:23.985 --> 01:24.951
Yes, ma'am.

01:27.345 --> 01:28.476
You can't go in there!

01:28.501 --> 01:30.067
I can and I will.

01:30.419 --> 01:31.751
What is she doing here?

01:32.531 --> 01:33.964
Mr. Briggs, I'm very sorry.

01:34.017 --> 01:35.683
Manhandle me and I won't hire you

01:35.718 --> 01:37.118
after he fires you for letting me in.

01:37.153 --> 01:38.386
I'm not gonna fire you.

01:38.421 --> 01:40.421
He might not, but banker
Barbie certainly will.

01:40.937 --> 01:42.000
She's right.

01:42.025 --> 01:44.258
You're supposed to keep this
house safe from lunatics.

01:44.283 --> 01:46.483
Uh, I got it, Pete. Thanks.

01:46.754 --> 01:47.720
Thank you, sir.

01:47.745 --> 01:48.945
Hello, Annie.

01:48.970 --> 01:51.137
What do you want?

01:51.302 --> 01:53.869
I just got an e-mail
from my head geologist

01:53.905 --> 01:56.500
about the land I bought
with Clifton and Billy.

01:56.525 --> 01:59.250
He tells me I just spent
a lot of money on dry land.

01:59.275 --> 02:01.475
Just as dry as your parcel, Harlan.

02:01.500 --> 02:04.067
If I listened to every
scientist that told me no,

02:04.092 --> 02:06.626
I wouldn't have half the fortune I have.

02:07.037 --> 02:09.537
Yet you'd also never
spend your time and money

02:09.562 --> 02:11.445
on anything that
wasn't a sure bet...

02:11.470 --> 02:13.103
Women or oil.

02:13.454 --> 02:15.454
I want to know what you know.

02:18.371 --> 02:21.046
I know the feds think
you've gotten your paws

02:21.071 --> 02:24.005
on a classified U.S.G.S. report,

02:24.030 --> 02:26.697
a report I'm quite certain would explain

02:26.722 --> 02:28.756
why that land is so valuable.

02:28.824 --> 02:31.976
Hap's told the feds, and he will tell you.

02:32.320 --> 02:34.754
He doesn't have the survey, Annie.

02:34.779 --> 02:37.580
It is so nice to hear
you defending your man.

02:37.615 --> 02:40.316
But I think I know how my ex does business.

02:40.351 --> 02:42.051
Give me a copy of the report

02:42.086 --> 02:44.353
and I'll make the problem
with the feds go away.

02:44.388 --> 02:47.156
I can't give you what I don't have.

02:48.100 --> 02:50.567
But why don't you sit
down and have some dinner?

02:50.930 --> 02:53.231
All that hostility must
have made you hungry.

02:53.563 --> 02:55.500
The problem with you, Harlan,

02:55.525 --> 02:58.827
is you've always underestimated your wives.

03:00.425 --> 03:02.559
And I've already eaten.

